President Muhammadu Buhari will on Friday travel to London, for a scheduled medical follow-up. Femi Adesina, Special Adviser on Media and Publicity to President Buhari, confirmed this in a statement on Thursday. Adesina said the President is expected return to the country in the second week of next month. “He is due back in the country during the second week of July, 2021,” the statement said. Recall that on Tuesday, March 30, 2021, Buhari had visited London to receive medical attention from his physician.